programme.title: Viking Velocity
programme.desc: Downhill racer Erik Lundberg has a gravity-fuelled dream to break the world skateboard speed record. To break the current world speed record on a skateboard, downhill racer Erik Lundberg will have to go faster than 129.95kph (80.7mph). It's a feat that will make him rethink his motivations, his equipment and his commitment to his goal.

programme.title: Freerunning in India
programme.desc: Ryan visits India for the first time and has some fun learning a new skill — Bollywood dancing. Ryan visits India for the first time and has some fun learning a new skill — Bollywood dancing. After mingling with the locals and jumping from city rooftops, Ryan does some parkour in front of the breathtaking Taj Mahal.

programme.title: AWOLNATION – Kill Your Heroes
programme.sub-title: Official music video from Red Bull Records
programme.desc: A group of kids are inspired to outrageous shenanigans by a group of bizarro-world Mister Rogers lookalikes. From their album Megalithic Symphony, AWOLNATION dresses up as a group of foul-mouthed, bizarro-world Mister Rogers lookalikes called The Milkmen and inspires a group of '60s children to rock-and-roll shenanigans.

programme.title: Roraima
programme.desc: A trio of climbers launch an expedition to Mount Roraima, a South American peak shrouded in legend. Climbing partners Kurt Albert and Holger Heuber don't know what they're in for when they join competitive climbing superstar Stefan Glowacz for an expedition to Mount Roraima, a steep-walled South American peak shrouded in both rainforest and legend.

programme.title: Ocean Blues
programme.desc: GZA, founder member of the hip-hop group Wu-Tang Clan, explores the idea of living at the bottom of the ocean. Host GZA wonders whether exploring the depths of our oceans might be the ultimate game changer for life on earth. Watch where this thought takes him as he searches for answers.

programme.title: The Last Chapter
programme.desc: It's the conclusion of another EWS season. Which of the select few will be victorious? The conclusion of another EWS season brings victory for only a select few. Sometimes the race doesn't go as hoped, but it's all about a love of riding.

programme.title: The Role of Role Play
programme.desc: Japanese role-playing games are responsible for some of the most iconic melodies in video game history. The drama and emotion in Japanese role-playing games have inspired some of the most iconic melodies in video game history. As a result, Nobuo Uematsu’s melodies from Final Fantasy have transcended video games, appearing in orchestral renditions.

programme.title: Run with the Flow
programme.sub-title: Chasing the Wings for Life World Record
programme.desc: Ultrarunner Florian Neuschwander is out to run a record 80km at the 2016 Wings for Life World Run. With a goal of breaking the 80km record and winning the 2016 Wings for Life World Run, ultrarunner Florian Neuschwander combines a non-conformist style with the passion of a man willing to run almost unimaginable distances.

programme.title: (WT) Recap Program Stop 1
programme.sub-title: MotoGP™: インサイドパス（知られざる舞台裏）エピソード1
programme.desc: Video-Blog aus dem Paddock #1 – Katar: Die MotoGP-Familie trifft sich wieder, die KTM-Rider beichten ihre Schnellfahr-Sünden und Michelin verrät Geheimnisse der Reifen bei Nachtrennen. Η host Vanessa Guerra θέλει να περιγράψουν οι αναβάτες το MotoGP™ με μία λέξη πριν ξεκινήσει ο πρώτος αγώνας της σεζόν στο VisitQatar Grand Prix. Η Vanessa Guerra πηγαίνει behind the scenes για να μάθει όλες τις αλλαγές στη νέα σεζόν του MotoGP™.

programme.title: Preparing for the unpredictable
programme.desc: We journey to Argentina with Vanessa Guerra and take a quick look at last year's unpredictably wet race.\t. We journey to Argentina with Vanessa Guerra and take a quick look at last year's unpredictably wet race before looking ahead to 2019. See the reaction time the riders have as they play a game and hear a little friendly competition between team-mates.

programme.title: Go-karting at Circuit of the Americas
programme.desc: The MotoGP™ riders are used to racing on two wheels, but how fast are they on four wheels? Vanessa Guerra is in Austin, Texas at Red Bull Grand Prix of the Americas, the third round of the MotoGP™ 2019 season. The riders are used to racing on two wheels, but how fast are they on four?

programme.title: Switzerland
programme.desc: Adam Trent pushes way outside his comfort zone and heads to Switzerland to do some paragliding in the Alps. It's off to the land of chocolate and cheese as Adam Trent goes to Switzerland to immerse himself in Swiss culture. After trying his hand at yodelling and watch making, a lead from Hungary winds up taking him to heights he never imagined.

programme.title: Moog
programme.desc: Inventor Bob Moog took the worlds of science and music and synthesised a seismic shift in the sonic landscape. Bob Moog, an inventor and technologist with an obsession with electronic instruments, blends science and music to create a seismic shift in the sonic landscape with a modular synthesiser that opens up a new world of musical possibilities.

programme.title: In the Balance
programme.desc: Trials rider and viral video star Danny MacAskill fights injuries to make his most ambitious film project. Trials rider and viral video star Danny MacAskill heads to Newport Beach, California to create the film project of his dreams, but old injuries in his back and knee keep limiting him on the bike. He's hoping rehab training in the gym will help.

programme.title: The Rules of Enduro
programme.desc: Curtis Keene's comeback, Sam Hill and suspension choice are all up for discussion in this round six preview. It's Specialized Racing's Curtis Keene's first race after injury at round six of the EWS in Aspen, Colorado. Curtis's comeback, Sam Hill and suspension choice are all up for discussion as we look ahead to some high-speed, high-altitiude action.

programme.title: The making of Wibmer’s Law
programme.desc: See how Fabio Wibmer and his crew film sequences that should end in a crash but turn into outstanding tricks. Unlike Murphy's Law, Fabio Wibmer's Law says: if it's possible for something to go wrong, it won’t go wrong. See how he and a film crew made Wibmer's Law a reality.

programme.title: Maja Kuczyńska
programme.desc: Seventeen-year-old Maja Kuczyńska is already more comfortable in the air than many career skydivers. Seventeen-year-old Maja Kuczyńska is already more comfortable dancing through the air than many longtime skydivers, but the first-ever Junior Indoor Skydiving World Champion has never actually jumped out of an aeroplane.

programme.title: Girl in the Boys Club
programme.desc: Amy Chmelecki shows what it takes to be the first – and only – female member of the Red Bull Air Force. As the first and only female member of the Red Bull Air Force, Amy Chmelecki brings unparalleled skill and a fierce competitive streak to every dimension of the sport. Here, she looks back on her path from novice to pro.

programme.title: To Modify on the Fly
programme.desc: In Las Vegas, the skydivers show the meticulous planning and last-second decisions that go into a demo jump. The Red Bull Air Force provides a behind-the-scenes look at the meticulous planning and last-second decision-making that goes into a set of demo jumps at some of Las Vegas’ most iconic landmarks.

programme.title: Ice Revolution
programme.desc: A pair of veteran ice climbers find the ultimate challenge in a massive cave in British Columbia, Canada. Canadian Will Gadd and Brit Tim Emmett discover a whole new universe of ice climbing at Helmcken Falls, Canada, where a 500ft waterfall sprays the underside of a gargantuan cave with fantastical, barely climbable ice formations.
